    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Radicalization Of James Woolsey</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brian Atkinson letter on Andrew Cockburn's July 23 article praises James Woolsey for standing up against US government in seeking to protect Iraqi men who face certain death if they are returned to their homeland</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>My thanks to Andrew Cockburn (July 23) for this chilling account of United States bureaucracy at work. You would not expect someone of James Woolsey's professional stature to encounter the difficulties he did in dealing with the Central Intelligence Agency and the Immigration and Naturalization Service. Fortunately, Woolsey is not afraid to say what he thinks.</p>
        <p>Brian Atkinson  Santa Ana, Calif.</p>
      </block>
